cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.RO, cs.MM 

This paper focuses on visual tracking, which is a subfield of computer vision. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also proposes a framework that leverages siamese feature extractors, which are commonly used in deep learning-based tracking methods. This suggests that the paper could also be relevant to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper discusses the performance and robustness of the proposed method, which are important considerations in robotics and control, indicating that cs.RO (Robotics) could also be a relevant sub-category. Finally, the paper evaluates its method on tracking benchmarks, which are commonly used in multimedia applications, suggesting that cs.MM (Multimedia) could also be a relevant sub-category.
